      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is powered by the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure dual-VANOS system. The powertrain is mated to a traditional 6-speed manual gearbox and an M Variable Differential Lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution. This example is mechanically robust, having received essential preventative maintenance including rear subframe reinforcement and a Vanos overhaul. The chassis retains its factory-spec kinematics, offering the precise turn-in and communicative feedback synonymous with the E46 platform. While the exterior shows honest wear consistent with a well-loved driver, the engine pulls hard to its 8,000 RPM redline with perfect compression. A visceral, analog machine for the serious driver.",
